\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/group.metacyclic}{Metacyclic group}}
\begin{definition}\label{group.metacyclic}
\uses{group.monomial,group.nonsplit_product,group.supersolvable,group.z_group}
A metacyclic group is an \hyperref[group.nonsplit_product]{extension} of a cyclic group by a cyclic group.  All metacyclic groups are \hyperref[group.supersolvable]{supersolvable} and in particular \hyperref[group.monomial]{monomial}. 

Every \hyperref[group.z_group]{Z-group} is metacyclic, but the converse does not hold, as shown by <a href="{{url\_for('abstract.index')}}?metacyclic=yes&Zgroup=no">these examples</a>.
\end{definition}


